						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Expecting things like EIST, CPU P-states, and GPU power-saving features to be disabled = wrong mentality for software design.</div><br />nemulator, if configured to do so (the default setting), will automatically disable CPU throttling upon startup, and restore the previous setting when exiting. So, I don't expect any particular configuration for it to work properly.<br /><br />Re: 50/75Hz settings - 50Hz with vsync is just never going to work. 75Hz should work, albeit not as smoothly as 60Hz. I'm not sure why the timer sync stuff isn't working for you. With it enabled, and vsync disabled, you should be running at a rock solid 59.97Hz...<br /><br />I found an LCD that will run at 75Hz. Will test on it when I get a chance.</div>

					
